&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Director, Growth Products&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Location: Charlotte, NC&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Home Solutions is seeking a Director of Growth Products to lead the development and optimization of the products, systems, and capabilities that power our customer acquisition engine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own a portfolio of internal and customer-facing products that influence how we acquire customers, convert traffic, monetize demand, and create value for consumers and service providers. At its core, your role will be to leverage our suite of proprietary products to improve conversion rates and lead quality across our network of enterprise partners.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Director of Yield Solutions you will identify opportunities, prioritize investments, and work closely with Engineering, Marketing, Revenue Operations, and Partnerships teams to bring ideas from concept to execution. We are seeking someone that can marry strong analytical skills and product management expertise to drive performance on one of most strategic initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Within your first year, you will have expanded our nascent product portfolio across our largest enterprise accounts, improved key acquisition and monetization metrics, and established yourself as a key driver of growth across Home Solutions. You will build and deploy systems that not only improve performance today but create durable competitive advantages for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Day-to-Day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own performance and expansion of products that support customer acquisition, lead generation, conversion, monetization, and marketplace efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to drive revenue growth through new products, product enhancements, automation, and emerging technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Engineering and Marketing to deploy and modify products that create measurable business impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop business cases for new product investments and growth initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze customer behavior, funnel performance, marketplace dynamics, and operational workflows to identify opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and execute experiments to validate hypotheses and improve performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Analytics to establish KPIs, monitor performance, and measure business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI, automation, and emerging technologies where appropriate to improve scalability, efficiency, and customer experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Turn ambiguous business opportunities into products that drive growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6–10+ years of experience in digital acquisition channels or&amp;nbsp; eCommerce. Cart optimization experience is a plus.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated track record of building and/or deploying products or capabilities that drove measurable business outcomes, including revenue growth, customer acquisition, conversion improvement, operational efficiency, or profitability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong product instincts with the ability to identify opportunities, prioritize investments, and balance short-term wins with long-term strategic value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience owning products from concept through launch, partnering closely with Engineering, Analytics, and Business teams to bring ideas to life.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing and executing experiments, A/B tests, or iterative product improvements to drive business performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of customer acquisition funnels, digital consumer behavior, and performance-driven business models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional structured problem-solving and business judgment.&lt;/

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Director of Strategy &amp;amp; Business Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Location: Charlotte, NC&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Home Solutions is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Director of Strategy &amp;amp; Business Operations&lt;/strong&gt; to own and drive high-impact initiatives across our customer acquisition business. This is a senior, cross-functional operator role at the center of the company. You will partner directly with leadership to identify where we should invest, what we should fix, and how we scale profitably. You will not just analyze the business — you will help run it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Director of Strategy &amp;amp; Business Operations, you will lead large initiatives that materially impact revenue, margin, and long-term enterprise value. Projects may span growth strategy, pricing, unit economics, vendor performance, customer experience, new market expansion, cost optimization, process design, and capital allocation. You’ll be expected to move seamlessly between strategy and execution — from diagnosing P&amp;amp;L performance to implementing structural improvements that stick.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Within your first year, you will have taken ownership of a meaningful portion of the business — leading multiple high-impact, cross-functional initiatives that drive sustained P&amp;amp;L improvement across revenue, margin, and marketplace performance. You will serve as a trusted partner to the executive team, shaping strategic priorities and making high-quality trade-off decisions in complex, high-stakes situations. You will have built durable systems, elevated operating standards, and developed team capabilities that increase the company’s long-term leverage — demonstrating smart judgment, leadership, and accountability required to run major components of the business at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and drive high-impact, cross-functional initiatives with clear P&amp;amp;L accountability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate, prioritize, and execute new growth opportunities across channels, markets, and services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set the roadmap for improving unit economics and marketplace efficiency across both consumer and service provider dynamics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify where we can unlock revenue, expand margins, or eliminate inefficiencies — and lead the implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Marketing, Product, Finance, and Operations to improve funnel performance, pricing strategy, and marketplace liquidity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and oversee the analytical infrastructure (models, dashboards, KPI frameworks) that informs executive decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead rigorous business cases for major investments, new markets, and expansion bets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor core P&amp;amp;L KPIs and proactively surface risks, trade-offs, and opportunities to the executive team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish scalable systems and processes that strengthen operational discipline as we grow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI and automation tools to increase team velocity, improve insight quality, and raise performance standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and mentor high-performing operators as the function scales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role combines strategic thinking, financial rigor, and hands-on execution. You will be accountable for outcomes — not presentations.&lt;/p&gt;
